<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911209-0145</DOCNO><DOCID>911209-0145.</DOCID><HL>   Lifetime Products   Acquires a System   For Fast Nail Drying</HL><DATE>12/09/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9A</SO><CO>   LPI</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>ADVERTISING, MARKETING, PUBLIC RELATIONS (ADV)AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)COSMETICS, PERSONAL CARE, OVER-THE-COUNTER REMEDIES (COS)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>ARIZONA (AZ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   DALLAS -- Lifetime Products Inc., broadening its productline beyond auto accessories, said it acquired a speedynail-polish drying system that it plans to market throughdirect mail and television ads.   The company, which is best known for its marketing of theTripledge windshield wiper, said it created a new subsidiary,Lifetime Cosmetics Inc., and bought the assets and trademarksfor the system from Ultraset L.P. and Ultraset Inc. ofPhoenix for a 15% stake in the unit. It also agreed to payroyalties to the former owners.</LP><TEXT>   Lifetime said it will continue to sell the SalonNail 3system to beauty salons. But the product, which now is soldthrough department stores for $59.95, will be sold direct for$29.95 beginning next year. The system includes two polishes,a base coat and a top coat, and a plug-in dryer. The companyclaims the nail polish dries in about three minutes.   The addition of a new product line comes at a time whenthe marketing company said it needs additional financing tocontinue its growth and meet its obligations. A spokesman forLifetime, which has grown rapidly, said that a fundingproposal has been prepared, but he declined to elaborate. Thecompany must spend about 57% of its monthly cash flow to meetits debt and interest payments to current and former officersand directors and to satisfy various employment andconsulting agreements.</TEXT></DOC>